---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import portrait from '../assets/aggie_ring.jpeg';
---

<Base title="About">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-xs font-mono text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl leading-tight">James Londrigan</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_260px]">
      <!-- Main content -->
      <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Howdy! I'm James Londrigan and I hail from a town just outside
          of Houston, Texas called Crosby. I grew up playing sports all
          through high school but my favorite one was baseball. I still
          watch all different kinds of sports, root for the Astros against
          all reason, and I still maintain that no rivalry compares to
          Aggies vs Longhorns.
        </p>
        <p>
          My dad worked in operational technology and I think that's where
          my interest in IT started. I came to Texas A&amp;M unsure of what
          path I wanted to take. I took ISTM 310 focused on networking and
          thought that was the path, but then the more I learned about
          cloud, the more it pulled me up the stack.
        </p>
        <p>
          Being an Aggie has done more for me than I can truly say. The
          obvious things are the visible ones — the ring, the traditions,
          the network. The part that's mattered most is the identity that
          doesn't come off when you graduate. I came in eighteen and not
          sure of much or of myself. I'm leaving with a Master's, a few
          certs, and a much clearer sense of who I am and what I want to do.
        </p>
        <p>
          Day to day: a year into the MS-MIS program at Mays, graduating
          December 2026, and chasing what cloud and AI can do for the
          businesses (and the people) on the receiving end of them. AWS
          certified three times over with Cloud Practitioner, AI Practitioner,
          and Solutions Architect Associate certs. I'm looking to expand this
          knowledge into Azure but that is still a work in progress. Most of
          the technical detail lives in the <a href="/projects"
          class="text-maroon hover:underline underline-offset-2">projects</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside of all that: at the gym most days trying to get stronger,
          I was deep in the <em>Red Rising</em> saga but need to finish the
          series still, and convinced my dog Houdini was named appropriately
          because he is a slippery little guy.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Sidebar -->
      <aside class="space-y-10">
        <!-- Portrait -->
        <Image
          src={portrait}
          alt="James Londrigan wearing his Texas A&M Aggie ring, making the Gig 'em hand signal"
          class="w-full aspect-square object-cover object-top"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
          widths={[260, 520]}
          sizes="260px"
        />

        <!-- Currently -->
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Currently</p>
          <dl class="space-y-3 text-sm">
            <div>
              <dt class="text-muted">Building</dt>
              <dd>This site — Astro, Terraform, AWS</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt class="text-muted">Reading</dt>
              <dd><em>Red Rising</em> series (still finishing)</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt class="text-muted">Learning</dt>
              <dd>Azure foundations</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
